# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // ~√(1/2)

// Physics configuration
var config = {
    attraction: 4000,
    frictionCoeff: 0.004,
    amplification: 0.92,
    dispersal: 0.0003,
    streamMax: 40,
    streamDecay: 0.04,
    theta: 0.06
};

// Graph nodes
var nodes = [
    { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Spring connections between nodes
var edges = [
    { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle stream
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics step: repulsion, springs, gravity, friction
function physicsStep() {
    // Node-node repulsion (inverse-square law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // Spring forces along edges
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // Gravity toward center (400, 300) + friction damping + integrate
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.dispersal;
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.dispersal;
        nodes[n].vx *= config.amplification;
        nodes[n].vy *= config.amplification;
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;

    var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: node.x,
        y: node.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update all particles (move, age, remove dead)
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
        p.vy *= (1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125);
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// Smooth camera interpolation toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
    physicsStep();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — a physics-based layout engine for a network of 6 nodes. Here's the breakdown:

### 🔵 Graph Structure
- **6 nodes**: Hub (central), Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon — each with position, velocity, and radius
- **8 edges** (springs): connecting the nodes, mostly radiating from Hub

### ⚙️ Physics Engine (runs every ~16ms)
1. **Repulsion**: Every pair of nodes repels each other via inverse-square force (like electric charges), preventing overlap
2. **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled toward each other with Hooke's law springs, each with a rest length and stiffness `k`
3. **Centering gravity**: All nodes are gently pulled toward center point (400, 300)
4. **Velocity damping**: Velocities are multiplied by 0.92 each frame (friction), so the system settles to equilibrium

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a particle spawns from a random node, flying outward at a random angle
- Particles slowly decelerate and die after 800–2000 frames
- Maximum 40 particles alive at once
- Creates a visual "streaming/emanating" effect around the graph

### 🎥 Camera
- Smoothly interpolates (`theta = 0.06` lerp factor) toward a target position/zoom, creating smooth panning

### In Summary
This is the **simulation backend** for an animated, interactive force-directed graph visualization with decorative particles — likely rendered on a canvas elsewhere. It computes the layout purely through physics without any rendering code present.
